<br>
The force produced by a rocket is simply the mass flow rate in kilograms multiplied by the exhaust velocity.<br>
<br>
F = mdot * Vex<br>
<br>
= 0.001 kg/sec * 900 000 m/sec<br>
<br>
= 900 Newtons = 91.77 kilograms = 202.3 pounds<br>
<br>
<br>
Vf = a * t<br>
<br>
Assuming S/C mass of 1 000 000 kg<br>
a = 0.0009 m/s/s<br>
<br>
If the S/C accelerates constantly for 1 year then Vf = 28.4067 km/sec<br>
<br>
However assuming your ship carries 500 000 kg of H2 and has a mass flow rate of 0.001kg/sec it will take you 15.84 years to consume all the propellant.<br>
<br>
In other words, you f*cked up big time.<br>
